  "name": "Luke 5:17–26",
  "localizedName": "Luke 5:17–26",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "A big crowd had come to hear Jesus teach. The house was so full of people that no one else could get in."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "A group of men had a friend who couldn’t walk. They wanted Jesus to heal him. They believed that Jesus had power over illness. The men didn’t give up. They lowered their friend through a hole in the roof right in front of Jesus."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Jesus saw how strongly they believed in his power to bring healing. Jesus called the man his friend and then forgave his sins. The religious leaders became angry. They didn’t believe that Jesus had the authority to "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108281",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "forgive"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " the man’s sins."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Then Jesus healed the man’s body. The man was so joyful that he praised God right away. Jesus came to earth to forgive sin, heal people and bring them close to God."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
